===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|abod|lang=enm}}, {{term|abad|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|*ābād}}, related to {{m|ang|ābīdan||to abide}}; see ''[[abide]]''. Cognate with Scots {{term|abade|lang=sco}}, {{term|abaid||abode|lang=sco}}. For the change of vowel, compare ''abode'', preterite of ''abide''.

